name: cenpy
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set version = "1.0.0.post4" %}

package:
  name: cenpy
  version: {{ version }}

source:
  url: https://pypi.io/packages/source/c/cenpy/cenpy-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 43d24ffbff6d1c2879a05499f2ac0776f10803524d466614cdec2cd3c9e9ff20

build:
  number: 0
  noarch: python
  script: {{ PYTHON }} -m pip install . --no-deps -vv

requirements:
  host:
    - python >=3.5
    - pip
  run:
    - python >=3.5
    - pandas
    - geopandas
    - requests
    - rtree
    - numpy
    - six
    - fuzzywuzzy
    - libpysal

test:
  imports:
    - cenpy

about:
  home: https://github.com/cenpy-devs/cenpy
  license: BSD-3-Clause
  license_family: BSD
  license_file: LICENSE
  summary: Explore and download data from Census APIs

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - ocefpaf
    - ljwolf
smithy_version:
No azure token. Create a token and
put it in ~/.conda-smithy/azure.token
